==English==

===Adjective===
'''contumelious'''

# Of or pertaining to rudely [[contemptuous]]; insolent; disdainful.
#:''The pad would not stay on Modestine’s back for half a moment. I returned it to its maker, with whom I had so contumelious a passage that the street outside was crowded from wall to wall with gossips looking on and listening.'' - [[:s:Travels with a Donkey in the Cévennes|Travels with a Donkey in the Cévennes]], Robert Louis Stevenson.

